Compile error today: Participants.tsx:30 references type User without importing it; npm run build fails. One-line fix at top of file: import type { User } from '../types';

Verify: npm run build is clean; npx eslint src/components/Participants.tsx reports no errors.

Trivially small. Ship first, no dependencies.

Frontend types follow the schema (sbc-1be):
export interface Room {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  slug: string;
  description: string | null;
  themeId: string;
  numChairs: number;
  visibility: 'public' | 'invite' | 'private';
  createdBy: string;
  createdAt: string;
}
export interface RoomMember {
  roomId: string;
  userId: string;
  role: 'owner' | 'admin' | 'member';
  joinedAt: string;
}

Also extend useStore types to track currentRoomId + currentRoom + roomsList.

